cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.HC, cs.IR 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques to extract biometric information from egocentric videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the potential applications of the proposed method in theft prevention and searching for videos shot by a specific person, which falls under the categories of Multimedia (cs.MM) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the privacy implications of sharing egocentric videos, which could be relevant to the categories of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC).
